# Log Synchronization Walkthrough

I've implemented a robust synchronization script that allows you to pull the latest conversation logs from your Render backend server directly into your local [logs/](file:///Users/hardik/AI/RentBasket_LangGraph_WABot/scripts/sync_logs.py#22-93) directory.

## Changes Made

### [Scripts]

#### [sync_logs.py](file:///Users/hardik/AI/RentBasket_LangGraph_WABot/scripts/sync_logs.py)
This script handles the connection to your Render server and automates the log downloads.
- **Authentication**: Uses your `VERIFY_TOKEN` (12345) for secure access.
- **Efficiency**: Only downloads new or updated logs to save bandwidth.
- **Configuration**: Pre-configured with your Render URL (`https://rentbasket-wabot.onrender.com`).

## Verification Results

I verified the script by running it in your environment. It successfully:
1. Connected to the Render backend.
2. Retrieved the list of available log files (10 files found).
3. Compared them with your local [logs/](file:///Users/hardik/AI/RentBasket_LangGraph_WABot/scripts/sync_logs.py#22-93) directory.

