## How to Use

### 1. Manual Sync (Once)
Run this whenever you want a quick update:
```bash
python3 scripts/sync_logs.py
```

### 2. Live Sync (Watch Mode)
Run this to keep it "automatic". It will check for new logs every 60 seconds (like a live feed):
```bash
python3 scripts/sync_logs.py --watch
```

> [!TIP]
> You can change the interval (e.g., every 30 seconds) using:
> `python3 scripts/sync_logs.py --watch --interval 30`
